<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>in on it • on it</xh5><p> <i>in on it</i>—(also: in at it) taking part in an activity; involved in smth.: We’re sure of one thing—it wasn’t a one-man job. But were there two, three, or four of them <u>in on it</u>?</p><p> <i>on it—</i>1. <i>(U.S. sl.)</i> well able to do smth.; in control of a situation or a task: You bet he could cook. He was just <u>on it</u>. 2. (<i>Austral. sl.)</i> drinking heavily: When he was <u>on it</u>, and wanted another drink ... he never had to press the bell, but pressed the button with a bullet.</p> </entry>
